{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6c2f0f96-379a-446a-9571-c121667136ed","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules defined in files listed *before* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing by swapping the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01LHwAKHw1NbxMVJbW55SFiy","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-d3ef9f58fd4f475998a5f0b05d87b34e/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-d3ef9f58fd4f475998a5f0b05d87b34e/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"f995209b-8956-4034-a422-a37c3792023c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed *before* them in the `.fsproj`. Currently, the order is:\n\n1. `Services.fs` — opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` hasn't been compiled yet\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` — uses both\n\nThe fix is to reorder so `Domain.fs` comes before `Services.fs`.","outputTokens":378,"requestId":"2817:2657B6:5C1AA0A:639628C:69FBE283"},"id":"0face8a8-1007-401e-a82e-edc7285c9d48","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:53:31.129Z","parentId":"2a64e89a-8b60-4ac6-b657-7f0f778af6dc"}
